      "inputType": "number",
      "correctAnswer": "3"
    }
  ],
  "hints": [
    "From $$ x + y = 7 $$, isolate one variable: $$ x = 7 - y $$.",
    "Substitute into $$ 4x - 3y = 7 $$ and solve for y first."
  ],
  "explanation": {
    "steps": [
      "1. From $$ x + y = 7 $$, write $$ x = 7 - y $$.",
      "2. Substitute into the first equation: $$ 4(7 - y) - 3y = 7 $$.",
      "3. Expand and combine terms: $$ 28 - 4y - 3y = 7 $$, so $$ 28 - 7y = 7 $$.",
      "4. Subtract 28: $$ -7y = -21 $$, then divide by -7: $$ y = 3 $$.",
      "5. Substitute back: $$ x = 7 - 3 = 4 $$.",
      "6. Check: $$ 4(4) - 3(3) = 16 - 9 = 7 $$ and $$ 4 + 3 = 7 $$ ✓"
    ]
  },
